nce","subChapters":[]},{"id":"b4d0489d-7b61-53b2-811c-9f71a109f675","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"bb01faee-7480-59d6-ad94-3d2e4231ce20","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"b7af2746-b98a-5b23-9899-92e414dd9fa1","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"14be2b03-6d56-532e-b297-13e31a7f53c8","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"96cc14fa-ddae-54b7-b119-55cc16d8b477","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"21bd8101-d235-5e7a-923f-20b44d3519b3","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"6f8d67ce-78cd-53b4-95f7-4e09a1be12c7","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"8d6bfdf9-ca2e-5b9c-9064-1d34cec1481b","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Management"},"subChapters":[{"id":"832fe969-b8f3-5575-b188-8bdc424d45ee","slug":"managing-recurrent-miscarriage","fullItemName":"Managing recurrent miscarriage","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 4dc326f3-babf-4786-9b0b-a8d500bdc388 --><h3>How should I manage a woman with recurrent miscarriage?</h3><!-- end field 4dc326f3-babf-4786-9b0b-a8d500bdc388 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 98c4a154-3fd4-44ea-8fa1-a8d500bdc37a --><!-- begin field c158b283-f6d9-40a1-b3ac-a8d500bdc388 --><ul><li><strong>Offer referral to investigate the cause of recurrent miscarriage for all women who have had:</strong><ul><li>Three or more miscarriages before 10 weeks of gestation.</li><li>One or more morphologically normal fetal losses occurring after 10 weeks gestation.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Advise that:</strong><ul><li>It may not be possible to determine the cause of recurrent miscarriage. However, women in whom no cause is found may be reassured that the prognosis for a future successful pregnancy is 75%.</li><li>Following referral, the woman is likely to be offered:<ul><li>Assessment for antiphospholipid antibodies and possibly other immunological abnormalities. If antiphospholipid antibodies are found, treatment with aspirin plus heparin will be considered in future pregnancies.</li><li>Investigations for genetic abnormalities in both partners.</li><li>Investigations for fetal genetic abnormalities (if fetal tissue is available).</li><li>Pelvic ultrasound scan to detect uterine abnormalities (such as fibroids).</li></ul></li><li>The following patient information leaflets produced by the Miscarriage Association may be helpful:<ul><li><a href=\"https://www.miscarriageassociation.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Recurrent-Miscarriage.pdf\" data-hyperlink-id=\"7fcc311b-e624-4016-8f9e-a8f701600bee\">Investigations following recurrent miscarriage (pdf)</a></li><li><a href=\"https://www.miscarriageassociation.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Antiphospholipid-syndrome-and-pregnancy-loss.pdf\" data-hyperlink-id=\"cfbb37b6-a7b5-4da8-a874-a8f701600c02\">Antiphospholipid syndrome and pregnancy loss (pdf)</a></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field c158b283-f6d9-40a1-b3ac-a8d500bdc388 --><!-- end item 98c4a154-3fd4-44ea-8fa1-a8d500bdc37a -->","subChapters":[{"id":"7ff24694-eb4a-5cc5-8290-85f2879e8f5f","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-f45","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5d75b894-6880-4034-ba7c-a8d500bdc393 --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field 5d75b894-6880-4034-ba7c-a8d500bdc393 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item f45bc566-5713-4fb3-b43c-a8d500bdc393 --><!-- begin field 6a3fc497-6df3-499e-be9e-a8d500bdc393 --><p>These recommendations are based largely on the Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists (RCOG) guideline <em>The investigation and treatment of couples with recurrent first-trimester and second-trimester miscarriage </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/miscarriage/references/\">RCOG, 2011</a>].</p><h5>Informing a woman with recurrent unexplained miscarriage about prognosis</h5><ul><li>This information is based on evidence from two high-quality cohort studies reviewed by the RCOG guideline development group (GDG)<em> </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/miscarriage/references/\">RCOG, 2011</a>].</li></ul><h5>Providing easily accessible information</h5><ul><li>This recommendation is based on expert opinion of the GDG of the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guideline <em>Ectopic pregnancy and miscarriage, </em>who felt that it was important that women should be able to access information easily<em> </em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/miscarriage/references/\">National Collaborating Centre for Women's and Children's Health, 2012</a>].</li></ul><!-- end field 6a3fc497-6df3-499e-be9e-a8d500bdc393 --><!-- end item f45bc566-5713-4fb3-b43c-a8d500bdc393 -->","subChapters":[]}]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}